title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.2: STRENGTHENING NATIONAL SOCIAL SAFETY NETS

description.narrative: Output 4.2: Scalable and flexible social protection delivery, targeting and M&E systems are in place at national level and in targeted counties to facilitate shock-responsive national social safety net programmes, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 4 - Social inclusion: An increased number of children from the poorest & most vulnerable households benefit from shock- responsive & integrated social protection interventions, as well as from child-specific policies

title.narrative: Output 4.2: Scalable and flexible social protection delivery, targeting and M&E systems are in place at national level and intargeted counties to facilitate shock-responsive national social safety net programmes

description.narrative: UNICEF continued to strengthen;Government social protection systems through disability-inclusive targeting, social protection monitoring and evaluation, consolidated beneficiary information management through the Enhanced Single Registry and coordination between county level programmes in health and nutrition with national systems. To enhance sector coordination, UNICEF continued to support GoK to bring together sector players through the Sector Group for Social Protection. UNICEF supported the Linkages and Referral Mechanisms within the social protection sector, thus enabling GoK to integrate linkages and a referral system that enhances overall shock responsiveness. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/12/2021
